column3: The Resistance has secured yet another outpost, and Dmitar would guide you there.
Speak with Dmitar at the western plateau.
A Resistance rank of <Value>IntegerParameter(1)</Value> is required to proceed with this quest.
Well come, Blade <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,2)/>. I see you've not been resting on your laurels since last we met.
We've secured a new outpost, and a barrier was erected over the site not long ago.
If you would follow me, I'll show you to our newest encampment. We've drawn perilously close to the <Emphasis>Dalriada</Emphasis> now, so be on your guard.
We are but a stone's throw from the <Emphasis>Dalriada</Emphasis>, much to the dismay of the IVth Legion, I would assume.
That their plans yet remain a mystery is concerning, but Master Garlond is confident in his countermeasures for any aerial assaults they may be plotting.
Victory is nearly at hand, Blade <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,2)/>, I can feel it!
There is no telling what manner of magitek weaponry the IVth Legion will employ in their desperation, but I have faith we will prevail in the end.
The Resistance front line advances, allowing you to participate in new skirmishes and critical engagements.
The next quest can be accepted by speaking with Bajsaljen after reaching Resistance rank <Value>IntegerParameter(1)</Value> or higher.
